liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Nominees for the 63rd Logie Awards have just been announced at Sydney's Museum of Contemporary Art. The ABC's Leigh Sales, Mark Coles Smith and Shaun Micallef are all up for the Gold Logie, but face some stiff competition from the likes of Hamish Blake, Julia Morris and Osher Günsberg. Blake and Morris are also nominated for Most Popular Presenter, as is Micallef and the ABC's Tony Armstrong. This year's awards will be returning to Sydney for the first time in 37 years — at The Star on Sunday, July 30. Here are the Most Popular award categories — the Most Outstanding ones will follow in our next post. liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Nominees for the 63rd Logie Awards will be announced this morning at the Museum of Contemporary Art in Sydney — and we'll bring them to you as soon as they arrive. Comedian Sam Pang (from The Front Bar and Have You Been Paying Attention?) is hosting this year, joining the likes of previous hosts Graham Kennedy, Bert Newton, Don Lane, Andrew Denton and Shaun Micallef. The awards will be broadcast on Sunday, July 30. The Logies returned last year after a three-year absence. Hamish Blake won the Gold Logie for Most Popular Personality on Australian TV, and also took home the inaugural Bert Newton award for most popular presenter. The ABC's Tony Armstrong won the Graham Kennedy award for Most Popular New Talent.
